Around 20 International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies (IFRC) staff are currently working in Tonga to help the country's disaster relief efforts. On Wednesday, they finally got in touch with the Pacific head of the delegation in Fiji, Katie Greenwood. During an interview with CGTN's You Yang, Greenwood shared details of the latest on Tonga's situation as well as the IFRC's disaster relief work on the ground.